Replace the legacy DEBUG_*_(ACQUIRE|RELEASE)_*_LOCK macro-based locking around libcwd debug object and debug channel registries with typed threadsafe constructs, using threadsafe::Unlocked read/write access for shared containers such as _private_::debug_objects and _private_::debug_channels while preserving the write-once/read-mostly initialization semantics of built-in channels such as dc::core and dc::fatal.
